## Vercel Web Analytics Implementation

Successfully installed and configured Vercel Web Analytics for the swapl project.

### Changes Made

**Modified Files:**

1. **app/layout.tsx** - Added Analytics component to the root layout
   - Imported `Analytics` from `@vercel/analytics/next`
   - Added `<Analytics />` component before the closing `</body>` tag
   - This follows the official Vercel documentation for Next.js App Router

2. **package.json** - Added dependency
   - Added `@vercel/analytics` version `^2.0.1`

3. **package-lock.json** - Updated with new dependency tree
   - NPM lock file updated with `@vercel/analytics` and its dependencies

### Implementation Details

- **Framework**: Next.js with App Router (detected from project structure)
- **Package Manager**: NPM (detected from package-lock.json)
- **Installation Source**: Official Vercel Analytics documentation (https://vercel.com/docs/analytics/quickstart)
- **Analytics Version**: @vercel/analytics@2.0.1

### Framework-Specific Configuration

Following the official Vercel documentation for Next.js App Router, the Analytics component was added to the root layout file (`app/layout.tsx`). This ensures analytics tracking is active across all pages of the application.

The implementation preserves the existing code structure:
- Maintained all existing imports and font configurations
- Kept the pure-static root layout pattern (no async operations)
- Added Analytics component as the last child in the body element

### Verification

✅ **TypeScript**: Type checking passed without errors
✅ **Linter**: ESLint passed (no new errors introduced)
✅ **Tests**: All 56 tests passed across 7 test suites
✅ **Dependencies**: Lock file successfully updated

### Next Steps for User

To complete the setup and start collecting analytics data:

1. **Enable Analytics in Vercel Dashboard**: 
   - Navigate to your Vercel project dashboard
   - Go to the Analytics section
   - Click "Enable" in the header

2. **Deploy the Application**:
   - Push these changes to your repository
   - Deploy to Vercel (automatic if connected to Git)
   - Or run `vercel deploy` from the command line

3. **Verify Installation**:
   - After deployment, visit your site
   - Open browser DevTools > Network tab
   - Look for requests to `/<unique-path>/view` confirming analytics is working

Analytics data will begin appearing in your Vercel dashboard after user visits accumulate.
